docs.abstract: The Trump administration has argued that economic security is national security. But as a consequence, it now finds itself in an economic war on nearly every front.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration has argued that economic security is national security. But as a consequence, it now finds itself in an economic war on nearly every front.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is increasingly blurring the line between America’s national and economic security, enabling him to harness powerful tools meant to punish the world’s worst global actors and redirect them at nearly every trading partner, including Mexico, Japan, China and Europe.

headline.main: Trump Mixes Economic and National Security, Plunging the U.S. Into Multiple Fights
headline.print_headline: In Name of Security, Trump Sets Off Economic Wars on Multiple Fronts

docs.abstract: An indictment in Brooklyn says a physician and a medical consultant were part of a network that enticed women to have surgery to bolster lawsuit settlements.
docs.snippet: An indictment in Brooklyn says a physician and a medical consultant were part of a network that enticed women to have surgery to bolster lawsuit settlements.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors in Brooklyn have charged a physician and the owner of a medical consulting firm over a scheme to persuade women to have their pelvic mesh implants surgically removed to bolster the value of lawsuits against the devices’ manufacturers.

headline.main: Two Men Charged in Pelvic Mesh Removal Scheme
headline.print_headline: 2 Men Charged With Fraud Over Pelvic Mesh Removals

docs.abstract: Bryan Carmody, a night-crawling stringer in the Bay Area, won the support of press-freedom activists, although he may not be a conventional journalist.
docs.snippet: Bryan Carmody, a night-crawling stringer in the Bay Area, won the support of press-freedom activists, although he may not be a conventional journalist.
docs.lead_paragraph: Bryan Carmody, the Bay Area freelance journalist whose house was raided by the police this month, was to get back his property that was seized — including his laptop and three decades’ worth of archives — following a hearing in San Francisco Superior Court on Tuesday.

headline.main: After Police Raid and a Hearing, a San Francisco Freelancer Will Get His Property Back
headline.print_headline: Police Will Return Materials Seized From Reporter in Raid
